## Third-Party Dependencies

Kalahari uses the following third-party libraries and frameworks. Each has its own license, listed below.

### Qt Framework - LGPL v3

Kalahari uses **Qt 6.5+** framework, licensed under GNU Lesser General Public License version 3 (LGPL v3).

**Important LGPL v3 Compliance:**
- Qt is **dynamically linked** (not static) to comply with LGPL v3 requirements.
- Users can replace Qt libraries with compatible versions.
- Qt source code is available from the official Qt website.

**Links:**
- Qt Homepage: https://www.qt.io/
- Qt Downloads: https://download.qt.io/official_releases/qt/
- Qt Licensing: https://www.qt.io/licensing/
- LGPL v3 Full Text: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.html

**Qt Components Used:**
- Qt6::Core - Core non-GUI functionality
- Qt6::Widgets - Widget classes for GUI
- Qt6::Gui - Base GUI classes (QPainter, QImage, etc.)

**Note:** If you redistribute Kalahari, you must include Qt dynamic libraries (.dll, .so, .dylib) and inform users they can replace them. See LGPL v3 for full requirements.

